1
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:11,833
<i> Felma, Felma!</i>

2
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:14,067
<i>Arjun, get the car
ready! Hurry!</i>

3
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>I suggest you go through
an executive checkup</i>

4
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:18,833
<i> as soon as you can.</i>

5
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:21,467
<i>Doctor, it's just
my head hurting.</i>

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,500
<i>Could you please listen
to the doctor?</i>

7
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,867
<i>- Dad.
- Go to Timo.</i>

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,433
<i>Tell him we're willing
to help him,</i>

9
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:29,567
<i> as long as he tells us</i>

10
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:30,967
<i>everything Hazel
ordered him to do.</i>

11
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,967
<i> Why are you here?</i>

12
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,100
<i>You won't get anything from me.</i>

13
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:35,767
<i> We promise we'll help you.</i>

14
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:39,067
<i> I can't risk my family's life.</i>

15
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,700
Didang!

16
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:48,533
Yes, what is it?

17
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:49,600
You didn't wake me up!

18
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:51,867
Hey, what are you saying
I didn't?

19
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,567
Why are you blaming me?

20
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:55,233
Why always my fault?

21
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:57,100
Come on, Didang!

22
00:00:57,233 --> 00:00:58,400
Relax.

23
00:00:58,533 --> 00:00:59,900
I tried to wake you up earlier.

24
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:03,233
You said, Didang,
give me five hours.

25
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:06,133
So I let you sleep
for five hours.

26
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:08,333
I said five minutes.

27
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,300
Huh?

28
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:10,567
Hours! Minutes!

29
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,867
- It's just a minutes?
- Minutes!

30
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,700
Sis, can I go with you to the
hospital?
I'll just change my clothes.

31
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:19,333
No, Coleen,
I'm in a hurry.

32
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:21,600
- Ma'am Felma.
- Mom?

33
00:01:21,733 --> 00:01:23,100
Mom.

34
00:01:23,967 --> 00:01:24,833
Mom, sorry.

35
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:26,633
I was about to go
and pick you up, Mom.

36
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:27,900
I was about to go
and pick you up.

37
00:01:28,033 --> 00:01:28,833
Where's Auntie?

38
00:01:28,967 --> 00:01:30,833
Weren't you supposed
to be together?

39
00:01:30,967 --> 00:01:32,167
She should've brought you home.

40
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:35,833
Dear, dear,
all the tests are done.

41
00:01:35,967 --> 00:01:37,967
The results
will come out tomorrow.

42
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,467
Your Auntie Paz
dropped me off here.

43
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:44,533
Besides, I'm feeling well now.

44
00:01:45,267 --> 00:01:47,600
Ah... wait for me.

45
00:01:47,733 --> 00:01:48,400
I'll just change my clothes.

46
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:50,800
Let's go to the office together.

47
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:52,933
Where's...

48
00:01:53,067 --> 00:01:54,167
Where's Jeffrey?

49
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:57,500
Joel picked him up early
this morning.

50
00:01:57,633 --> 00:01:59,533
Where would they go?

51
00:02:03,633 --> 00:02:05,267
Timo, don't be afraid
to tell us.

52
00:02:06,467 --> 00:02:09,467
Because if Hazel's
threatening you,

53
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,967
then we are your only hope,
Timo.

54
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:13,233
Get out of here!

55
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:14,467
I don't even know you!

56
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,700
You won't get anything from me!

57
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:24,600
Just help my wife
and kids, okay?

58
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:26,833
And my mom.

59
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:30,500
I said stop!

60
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,133
Won't you leave?

61
00:02:33,267 --> 00:02:35,033
I don't know you!

62
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,033
If you want to know the truth,

63
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:40,133
come back tomorrow.

64
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:42,800
Aren't you leaving?

65
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:43,800
Are you guys crazy?

66
00:02:43,933 --> 00:02:44,967
What's this, boss?

67
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:45,900
I don't know them!

68
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:46,800
No, no, we're leaving.

69
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:49,133
We're leaving now, thank you.

70
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:51,400
- We're leaving, Sir.
- Who are they, Sir?

71
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:19,133
Does Manuel know
what you're going through?

72
00:03:19,267 --> 00:03:21,300
Ah...

73
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:23,133
No.

74
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:26,267
I told Jeffrey not to tell him.

75
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,967
I don't want to add
to his burdens.

76
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:33,533
Ah, you're keeping it
from Manuel.

77
00:03:33,667 --> 00:03:36,100
But not with Noah?

78
00:03:36,233 --> 00:03:44,600
Oh, I get it, confirmed.

79
00:03:44,733 --> 00:03:46,133
What is?

80
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:52,200
The truth that Manuel
is still the one you love.

81
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:55,667
Right? You don't want
to burden Manuel,

82
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:59,133
but it's okay if it's Noah?

83
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:06,100
Oh, Sis, I don't say
you're using Noah, okay?

84
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:07,200
It's not like that.

85
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,833
Because we both know you don't.

86
00:04:09,967 --> 00:04:14,167
I know Noah helps willingly.

87
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:17,000
Even if you drive him away,

88
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:19,467
he will never turn
his back on you.

89
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:23,067
My only point is, sis...

90
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,733
As your best friend...

91
00:04:25,867 --> 00:04:28,300
it's okay if you burden me.

92
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,333
It's okay, just lean on me.

93
00:04:32,367 --> 00:04:35,067
I will even carry you
if you want.

94
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,900
Just don't always rely
on Noah, okay?

95
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,100
I don't want to burden...

96
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:43,700
anyone of you, sis.

97
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:49,267
So... stop lecturing me.

98
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,700
Because I still have
a lot to finish.

99
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,033
You're distracting me.

100
00:04:54,167 --> 00:04:55,233
Ouch!

101
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:57,067
So am I the burden now?

102
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:58,833
Really?

103
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:00,233
Okay, Madam.

104
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,600
Go back to work.

105
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:02,967
I'll submit
to the accounting department,

106
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:05,067
these papers that you signed.

107
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:07,833
Okay.

108
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:10,633
Would you like
some coffee, Madam?

109
00:05:10,767 --> 00:05:11,533
- No thanks.
- Water?

110
00:05:11,667 --> 00:05:12,667
Thank you.

111
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,700
Jeffrey...

112
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,567
Do you think
Timo will give in...

113
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:29,233
and confirm Aunt Felma
and Uncle Manuel's suspicion?

114
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,700
I'm not sure.

115
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:35,200
He looks desperate, Bro.

116
00:05:36,433 --> 00:05:38,767
And he seems to be scared
for his family.

117
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:44,300
I hope Timo becomes convinced
that we'll help him.

118
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:48,067
So he can tell us the truth.

119
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,067
But if he's going to speak up,

120
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:50,900
why didn't he do it earlier?

121
00:05:51,033 --> 00:05:52,267
Why tomorrow?

122
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,767
I don't know.

123
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:58,533
Hazel might have people inside.

124
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:01,400
And she knows
a corrupt police officer.

125
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:03,467
Right? So maybe
he has men inside.

126
00:06:04,633 --> 00:06:06,933
Maybe Timo's just being careful.

127
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,567
That's possible.

128
00:06:10,067 --> 00:06:11,367
We'll find out tomorrow.

129
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:20,833
Hello?

130
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,167
Why did you call?

131
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:29,667
Jeffrey Cruz? Joel Santiago?

132
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,400
Yes.

133
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:33,633
But they didn't stay long,
Ma'am.

134
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:36,067
I think it's less than
two minutes.

135
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,100
Timo sent them away.

136
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:40,100
Did they see me earlier?

137
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:41,833
I don't know, Ma'am.

138
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,633
But I don't think so.

139
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:46,133
Because Timo didn't
tell them anything.

140
00:06:46,267 --> 00:06:48,167
For now, nothing.

141
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,133
What about their next visits?

142
00:06:50,267 --> 00:06:51,867
What do I do, Ma'am?

143
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,433
Should I take care of him?

144
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:57,033
No! What do you think of me?
A murderer?

145
00:06:57,167 --> 00:06:58,800
Just scare him.

146
00:06:58,933 --> 00:07:01,000
I just did, Ma'am.

147
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:02,167
My hands were itching.

148
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,433
It actually got tired already.

149
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,067
<i> Then teach him a lesson again.</i>

150
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:08,467
But this time, use your feet.

151
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:12,300
So that it'll be clear to him
that he can't speak the truth.

152
00:07:12,433 --> 00:07:13,467
Okay, Ma'am.

153
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,700
Please stop, please stop.

154
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:20,833
I'm begging you.

155
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:27,967
Sir, please stop!

156
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:33,633
Sir, please stop!

157
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:46,500
This is your CT scan report,
Miss Felma.

158
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:56,500
And this one concerns us.

159
00:07:58,333 --> 00:07:59,800
What is it, Doc?

160
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,267
Tumor located here.

161
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:09,467
Basing it on the density
and borders,

162
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:14,333
it's likely to be
a frontal lobe tumor

163
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:15,800
in your brain.

164
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:23,300
I have a brain tumor, Doc?

165
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,033
How's your mom's checkup?

166
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:41,467
They'll find out today.

167
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:44,733
Mom is in the hospital.

168
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,167
Felma's sick?

169
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:49,800
What's her illness?

170
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:50,900
Are you concerned?

171
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,933
I'll be a hypocrite
if I say yes.

172
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:56,633
I'm just curious.

173
00:08:56,767 --> 00:08:59,567
Jeffrey, I welcomed you
to my house.

174
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,367
Please don't be rude.

175
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,067
I'm not being rude.

176
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,333
Hazel, come on.

177
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:06,700
Leave us for now.

178
00:09:07,967 --> 00:09:09,900
Just call me
if you need anything.

179
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,867
This tumor, Miss Felma...

180
00:09:22,067 --> 00:09:23,967
could be the root cause
of your symptoms.

181
00:09:25,767 --> 00:09:30,600
Because it's pushing
the tissues around it.

182
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:33,633
The location is critical.

183
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:37,933
The frontal lobe controls...

184
00:09:38,067 --> 00:09:45,533
our judgment, behavior, memory,
and motor functions.

185
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:49,333
We will schedule further imaging

186
00:09:49,467 --> 00:09:52,067
To see the tumor's
boundaries clearly.

187
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,100
After that...

188
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,833
we can determine whether...

189
00:09:57,900 --> 00:10:00,467
the safest approach
would be the medication...

190
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:02,967
surgical, or...

191
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,033
Doctor...

192
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:08,067
am I going to have surgery?

193
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,467
Ah...

194
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,433
That is our long-term solution,
Ms. Felma.

195
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:16,567
It's called surgical resection.

196
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:21,100
Then once we remove the tumor,

197
00:10:21,233 --> 00:10:23,433
we will send it
to histopathology

198
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:26,133
to determine if it's benign
or malignant.

199
00:10:27,367 --> 00:10:29,800
Our next steps
will depend on it.

200
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:34,767
How safe is the operation?

201
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:36,500
We have advanced equipment.

202
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:39,433
Complete monitoring

203
00:10:39,567 --> 00:10:42,767
and an experienced
neurosurgical team.

204
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:45,933
We'll do everything

205
00:10:46,067 --> 00:10:47,800
to save Ms. Felma's life.

206
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:53,767
But you need to understand

207
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:59,167
that there is no zero
risk brain operation.

208
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,033
Felma.

209
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,400
Excuse me.

210
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:10,500
Felma!

211
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:17,533
Felma, Felma.

212
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:18,500
Felma.

213
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:20,367
Felma, are you okay?

214
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,200
Felma.

215
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,567
Are you okay?

216
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:25,767
I don't want...

217
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:28,800
I don't want surgery.

218
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:30,533
Noah, no.

219
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:32,467
I might not wake up.

220
00:11:34,533 --> 00:11:35,600
Felma...

221
00:11:37,567 --> 00:11:41,167
What... What do I do, Noah?

222
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:44,167
I think you need
to tell the kids.

223
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:46,600
No.

224
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:50,100
We just got through
Coleen's problem.

225
00:11:50,233 --> 00:11:53,700
And then, Manuel left us.

226
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,433
Felma, they need to know.

227
00:11:57,567 --> 00:11:59,100
It's their right.

228
00:12:00,767 --> 00:12:02,400
I know, but...

229
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:04,033
but...

230
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,100
I don't want to tell them yet.

231
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:15,900
How about Manuel?

232
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:22,300
I hope Timo tells the truth.

233
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:25,333
And I really hope my and Felma's
suspicion was correct.

234
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,433
Yes, Dad.

235
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,133
Later.

236
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:30,300
We'll find out later.

237
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:33,767
That is, if he doesn't
get scared.

238
00:12:34,967 --> 00:12:37,400
If his life
is threatened inside,

239
00:12:37,533 --> 00:12:39,567
Colonel Sarabia must know.

240
00:12:41,067 --> 00:12:42,133
Okay, Dad.

241
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:44,333
Remember to keep it between us.

242
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:48,133
Don't tell Coleen and Andrea,
especially your mom.

243
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:50,367
I don't want her to worry.

244
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,667
Yes, Dad.

245
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,533
Alice...

246
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:00,333
I need to move fast.

247
00:13:00,467 --> 00:13:02,433
These three won't leave me alone

248
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:05,567
until they dig up
the truth about Timo.

249
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:10,433
I'll speed things up.

250
00:13:22,467 --> 00:13:24,867
I will only add to his worries.

251
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:28,733
And Hazel's with him now.

252
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,667
He doesn't need...

253
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,633
to know what's happening to me.

254
00:13:35,133 --> 00:13:39,667
Noah, I don't want anyone else
to know about this yet.

255
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,800
Okay.

256
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:42,333
Let's keep it between us.

257
00:13:43,667 --> 00:13:44,800
For now.

258
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:48,700
And let's deal with it together.

259
00:13:51,767 --> 00:13:53,700
Let's go back to the doctor.

260
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:57,033
No.

261
00:13:57,167 --> 00:13:59,500
He will just say the same thing.

262
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:01,400
I have a tumor,

263
00:14:01,533 --> 00:14:03,933
and I need surgery.

264
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:05,367
I want...

265
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,567
a second opinion.

266
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:08,833
Okay.

267
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,133
Emil, my cousin,

268
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:15,033
is one of the top
neurologists in Davao.

269
00:14:15,167 --> 00:14:16,333
I can ask him to come here.

270
00:14:17,733 --> 00:14:20,267
Felma, are you okay now?

271
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:23,967
Since you don't want
to go back inside,

272
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:26,633
do you want us to go home now?
So you can get rest.

273
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,633
I don't want to go home yet.

274
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:34,433
Let's go watch a movie?

275
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:37,033
Huh? Movie?

276
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:38,733
Yes.

277
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:40,800
Let's watch a movie.

278
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:43,800
Then let's go to a spa.

279
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:46,733
It's been a while
since I last had a massage.

280
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:49,400
Then let's have coffee.

281
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,467
Okay, let's do that.

282
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,833
Okay, let's go?

283
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:57,633
The car's over there.

284
00:14:57,767 --> 00:14:59,167
Come on.

285
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:18,133
What are you going to do
with my passport?

286
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,567
Manuel...

287
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:32,700
I need details.

288
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:36,600
I'm booking a ticket to Taiwan.

289
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:41,000
Let's take a vacation.

290
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:43,900
You know, we deserve a break.

291
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:45,633
We need to take a rest.

292
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,267
Vacation in Taiwan?

293
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,400
Or are you bringing me
back to Canada?

294
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,033
Taiwan.

295
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:55,300
Vacation, Manuel.

296
00:15:56,967 --> 00:16:01,233
Manuel, there's no reason for us
to go back to Canada.

297
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:02,667
I had our house sold.

298
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:05,400
Don't you believe me?

299
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:11,300
How do you think
we can afford this house

300
00:16:11,467 --> 00:16:14,033
f we'll only rely
on my transcription job?

301
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:17,200
Hazel, I don't want
to go on vacation.

302
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:18,333
But Manuel...

303
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:19,700
I said no!

304
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:23,500
Okay, Don't get mad.

305
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:26,000
All right.

306
00:16:28,367 --> 00:16:29,233
Ah.

307
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,700
By the way,

308
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:36,133
Your firstborn was here earlier.

309
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:37,467
What did you two talk about?

310
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:41,700
Why are you interested?

311
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:43,533
Am I not allowed to ask?

312
00:16:45,467 --> 00:16:47,100
What do you need to know?

313
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:49,833
Oh, no.

314
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,167
Why?

315
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:53,267
Did he say something...

316
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,867
you're not supposed to tell me?

317
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:57,200
Like what?

318
00:16:58,633 --> 00:16:59,533
I don't know.

319
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:01,333
That's why I'm asking.

320
00:17:02,467 --> 00:17:05,100
What could my son possibly say
that you need to hear?

321
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:10,633
<i> Jeffrey Cruz? Joel Santiago?</i>

322
00:17:12,567 --> 00:17:14,167
Manuel...

323
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:16,167
nothing.

324
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,533
Come on.

325
00:17:17,667 --> 00:17:19,033
We'd better get ready.

326
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:22,167
You might get late
for your therapy session.

327
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,400
Go on.

328
00:17:24,933 --> 00:17:26,733
How's Diana?

329
00:17:30,100 --> 00:17:35,900
I gave Diana and her kids their
financial support in advance.

330
00:17:36,033 --> 00:17:37,133
I even give them
additional money

331
00:17:37,267 --> 00:17:39,833
for Diana's hospital expenses.

332
00:17:39,967 --> 00:17:42,700
I also visited Timo yesterday.

333
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,633
I brought him some groceries.

334
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:47,667
Okay, Manuel.

335
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,067
I'll get ready now.

336
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,367
Hello?

337
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:26,467
You're burning hot.

338
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:30,467
Son of a gun.

339
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,400
Looks like Alonzo's
going to kill you.

340
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:39,367
Bro...

341
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,100
What's this?

342
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:53,333
What's this?

343
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:55,100
It's the thing we talked about.

344
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,067
It's dangerous, bro.

345
00:19:05,967 --> 00:19:07,233
I'm begging you.

346
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:08,267
Please help me.

347
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:13,900
No, bro,
I might get caught.

348
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,267
Alonzo might pick on me next.

349
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:18,133
For my wife and kids' sake.

350
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:20,000
I'm begging you.

351
00:19:20,133 --> 00:19:21,533
Please help me, bro.

352
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:26,867
Please.

353
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,067
Darn it.

354
00:19:29,367 --> 00:19:30,367
Fine, I will.

355
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:35,167
After this...

356
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:37,367
I'm staying out of your problem.

357
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:40,700
Thank you, thank you.

358
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:51,167
Oh.

359
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:58,500
- What?
- Oh?

360
00:19:58,633 --> 00:20:00,333
- Why?
- No...

361
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:02,800
I remember the movie we watched.

362
00:20:02,967 --> 00:20:03,700
- Oh?
- You know,

363
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,467
It's weird.

364
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:08,567
I thought it was a horror.

365
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,533
Oh.

366
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:11,933
Looked like
you didn't get scared.

367
00:20:12,067 --> 00:20:14,033
I got annoyed with Arjun

368
00:20:14,167 --> 00:20:15,733
because it was
his recommendation.

369
00:20:15,867 --> 00:20:17,533
I want you to get scared.

370
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:18,500
Oh really?

371
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:19,800
- Yes.
- You want me to get scared?

372
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:21,767
- Yes.
- Seriously? Why...

373
00:20:21,900 --> 00:20:23,300
- And so...
- Do you want a horror film?

374
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:26,133
- What for?
- So that it'll be more fun.

375
00:20:27,467 --> 00:20:28,233
What do you mean by more fun?

376
00:20:28,367 --> 00:20:29,633
Is it fun for me to get scared?

377
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:31,567
- What now?
- Shouldn't it be?

378
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,200
Felma?

379
00:20:37,133 --> 00:20:38,633
Noah?

380
00:20:38,767 --> 00:20:39,700
Wow.

381
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,900
What a coincidence.

382
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:44,033
What a small world.

383
00:20:44,167 --> 00:20:45,533
'Andito rin pala kayo?

384
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:50,567
Oh, Manuel.

385
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:51,833
Felma seems to be doing well.

386
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:55,133
Look, she's even having
a date with Noah.

387
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:58,467
You know what?

388
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,667
You look good together.

389
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:02,733
As in, you really suit
each other well.

390
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:05,967
Mind if we share a table?

391
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,233
If you want to.

392
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:11,333
- No!
- No!

393
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:15,900
Oh, wow.

394
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:17,800
That was an intense reaction.

395
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:20,433
Don't you want
the four of us together?

396
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:22,200
Like a double date?

397
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,700
Hazel.

398
00:21:36,267 --> 00:21:39,133
Has Auntie Felma
given an update?

399
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:40,467
Yes, she texted earlier.

400
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,567
She said everything is normal.

401
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:45,333
Even her lab tests.

402
00:21:45,467 --> 00:21:48,267
She was advised to get some rest
to alleviate her stress.

403
00:21:56,833 --> 00:21:58,933
Bro, I'm sorry.

404
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,467
Malabanan can't meet you
right now.

405
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:03,500
Huh?

406
00:22:03,633 --> 00:22:06,200
Do you know why, Sir?

407
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:08,067
He's sick.

408
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,967
But, Sir,
he was doing well yesterday.

409
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,767
I don't know, bro.

410
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:14,800
He doesn't want to get up.

411
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:16,433
I think he's having
an upset stomach.

412
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:21,900
Okay, Sir, ah...

413
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:24,833
Maybe we'll just
come back tomorrow.

414
00:22:24,967 --> 00:22:26,100
Thank you, Sir.

415
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,267
Son of a...

416
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,800
Are you blind, you jerk?

417
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:33,267
I didn't mean it.

418
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:35,200
No? Bastard!

419
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:36,333
Hey! Let go of me!

420
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:37,833
- He's hurt...
- You're crazy.

421
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:39,333
Wait a minute.

422
00:22:39,467 --> 00:22:40,600
Come over here.

423
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:48,000
You call can leave now.

424
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,233
Visting hourse are over.
